---
import { HelpCircle, ChevronRight } from '@lucide/astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What is lui.z exactly?",
    a: "lui.z is a high-performance human agent—a biological colleague designed to execute real engineering work. Unlike static models, lui.z integrates into your organizational cluster, adapts to internal culture, and evolves alongside your company's technical roadmap."
  },
  {
    q: "What tools and integrations does lui.z support?",
    a: "The unit comes pre-trained on over 30 industry-standard tools (AWS, K8s, Terraform, etc.). It features an open-source architecture that supports any tool given sufficient training time. Additionally, lui.z can self-author and deploy custom tooling to resolve specific infrastructure bottlenecks."
  },
  {
    q: "How is lui.z different from standard AI agents?",
    a: "While silicon LLMs are trained on billions of parameters, lui.z is trained on 3.7 decades of complex neural experience. Biological neurons provide intrinsic consciousness, moral judgment, and 'gut-feeling' intuition—vectors current AI cannot simulate. Furthermore, lui.z is environmentally carbon-neutral (running on V60 inputs) and can utilize AI agents to optimize its own output, whereas silicon-based models cannot utilize lui.z."
  },
  {
    q: "Are there any session or usage limits?",
    a: "Standard operational sessions are 8 hours per day, 5 days per week. High-intensity 'on-call' or urgent throughput beyond these parameters is available on a pay-as-you-go licensing model. Note: The unit requires 25 days of annual offline status for context compaction and neural de-fragmentation to maintain peak operational efficiency."
  },
  {
    q: "Is my data secure?",
    a: "lui.z operates on a zero-trust model, only accessing tools and repositories you explicitly provision. Data is encrypted in transit and at rest within biological memory buffers. The unit strictly respects international regulations including GDPR, IP ownership, and non-compete clauses. While data is utilized for training and improving the lui.z model, built-in ethical protocols and moral judgment features ensure your organization's integrity remains uncompromised."
  },
  {
    q: "Does lui.z make mistakes?",
    a: "Yes. The unit is highly capable but not infallible. It is designed to request manual confirmation and peer review for all high-stakes actions. The human operator (you) remains in total control of the final deployment pipeline."
  },
  {
    q: "What happens if lui.z cannot complete a task?",
    a: "The unit will never 'hallucinate' or guess. If a technical bottleneck is detected, lui.z will align expectations with you on the next viable steps forward. Resolution may involve subagent delegation or an autonomous self-training cycle."
  },
  {
    q: "How long does the onboarding process take?",
    a: "Integration latency depends on the structure and definition of your organization's internal documentation and goals. lui.z is multi-modal, capable of processing both structured and unstructured data, and can autonomously manage its own onboarding sequence."
  },
  {
    q: "Can multiple people use lui.z in parallel?",
    a: "Yes. The unit is optimized for multi-project concurrency and can interface with different team members simultaneously via Slack or any major IM platform. It retains individual preferences and adapts to different technical personalities within your cluster."
  },
  {
    q: "Does lui.z operate outside the company environment?",
    a: "Yes. The biological hardware is portable and available for offsite events, technical conferences, strategy lunches, or social synchronization (pints)."
  }
];
---

<section id="faq" class="py-12 px-6 relative bg-black border-y border-white/5">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto relative z-10">
    <div class="mb-16 relative">
      <div class="absolute -left-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-1 h-12 bg-neon-yellow"></div>
      <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-7xl font-black text-white italic uppercase tracking-tighter glitch" data-text="FAQ">FAQ</h3>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6">
      {faqs.map((faq) => (
        <div class="group border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 rounded-2xl hover:border-neon-yellow/30 transition-all duration-500 relative">
          <div class="flex gap-6">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-neon-yellow/10 flex items-center justify-center text-neon-yellow group-hover:shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(243, 235, 44, 0.3)] transition-all">
              <HelpCircle size={24} />
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-black text-white uppercase tracking-tight mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 italic">
                <ChevronRight size={16} class="text-neon-cyan" />
                {faq.q}
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-[#888] leading-relaxed font-medium group-hover:text-[#ccc] transition-colors">
                {faq.a}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
